<StaticPageLayout
  title="Contact"
  description="Send corrections, test suggestions, access offers, and the occasional strongly worded pricing-page update."
  kicker="No mystery form"
>
  <h2>Email</h2><p>
    Write to <a href="mailto:x771364026@gmail.com">x771364026@gmail.com</a>. Please include the page
    URL and enough detail for us to reproduce the issue.
  </p>
  <h2>Make a correction useful</h2><p>
    Include the page URL, the exact sentence or data point, a primary source, and the date you
    checked it. “Your review is wrong” is emotionally clear but operationally thin.
  </p>
  <h2>Vendor access</h2><p>
    Tell us whether the account is free, temporary, or restricted. Providing access does not
    guarantee coverage, timing, or a favorable result.
  </p>
</StaticPageLayout>
